  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (coverage gap adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation results span the nominal operating envelope (2–5 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM); high-shear-stress regions at impeller tip clearances and extreme low-flow stall conditions named in the COU are noted as studied separately, but no linked evidence for those edge cases is provided in this package.",
