    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required gradation levels for MRL 2. Six factors are not assessed, consistent with MRL 2 scoping allowances. Validation results across the five nominal operating points (2–5 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM) demonstrate RH prediction errors below 5%. The credibility assessment team concludes the model is sufficiently credible for the COU decision. High-shear-stress tip clearance and extreme low-flow stall edge cases referenced in the COU intended use are noted as addressed in a separate internal study, and the overall evidence package is deemed acceptable for regulatory submission at MRL 2.",
